Introduction

IMFACT is a South Korean boy group that debuted as a five-member group under Star Empire Entertainment on January 27, 2016, with their single album Lollipop.

On January 4, 2022, the members chose not to renew their contracts with Star Empire Entertainment, parting ways with the agency. However, the group has not officially disbanded. The name IMFACT combines "Impact" and "I'm Fact," symbolizing their goal to make a strong impression on the music industry and create authentic music.
